Looking at my Symbolic Regression code, I realize that it's been using 
some of these operators for a very long time - it's equiped with 
Sigmoid, Gaussian, ADD and Multiply to solve the problems.

I'd have to run maaany long runs to determine if it helps or not, and 
I'm not in a possition to do that right now.

DelphiNEAT is a pretty straight forward implementation of NEAT, and 
these operators / transfer functions are simple an alternative way of 
using the input to determine the output. 

cheers,
mattias
